40 law to change a general rate schedule to authorize a natural gas utility to file an application to
41 establish an alternative rate-making plan pursuant to section 12.
42 Existing law requires the Commission to adopt regulations to establish procedures
43 for an electric utility to apply to the Commission for the approval of an alternative rate-
44 making plan. (NRS 704.762) Section 16 of this bill requires that, if an electric utility files
45 an application for an alternative rate-making plan that includes formula rates or a
46 multi-year rate plan, the alternative rate-making plan must include: (1) an earnings-
47 sharing mechanism; and (2) certain information and calculations relating to changes in
48 risk to the electric utility.
49 Existing law authorizes an electric utility to apply to the Commission to establish an
50 alternative rate-making plan and sets forth certain requirements relating to the
51 approval of the plan by the Commission. (NRS 704.7621) Section 17 of this bill requires
52 that, if the Commission approves an application for an alternative rate-making plan that
53 authorizes the recovery of the costs of a capital expenditure: (1) the electric utility must
54 prove the capital expenditure was prudent; and (2) if the Commission determines that
55 the electric utility did not prove the capital expenditure was prudent, the Commission
56 shall require the electric utility to refund the costs of the capital expenditure charged to
